description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dental Academic Recruitment 2021&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NIHR Academic Clinical Fellowship in DCT 1-3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specialty/Function:&lt;/strong&gt;Dental Core Training (DCT1-3) in Special Care Dentistry, Paediatric Dentistry &amp; Restorative Dentistry&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Indicative posts:&lt;/strong&gt;1&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duration:&lt;/strong&gt;3 years to commence September 2021.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employer:&lt;/strong&gt;Lead Employer Trust hosted by Northumbria Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt;Newcastle University’s School of Dental Sciences, Newcastle upon Tyne Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary:&lt;/strong&gt;NHS Medical &amp; Dental&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Type:&lt;/strong&gt;Fixed Term Temporary&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Group:&lt;/strong&gt;Medical &amp; Dental&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay Scheme:&lt;/strong&gt;Hospital Medical &amp; Dental Staff&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Allowances:&lt;/strong&gt;To be confirmed on appointment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applications Open: 27th October at 16:00pm&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applications Close:&lt;/strong&gt; 10th November at 16:00pm&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Date:&lt;/strong&gt;TBC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a NIHR Academic Clinical Fellowship in Dental Core Training (Special Care Dentistry, Paediatric Dentistry and Restorative Dentistry) within Health Education England working across the North East and North Cumbria, to start September 2021. The post holder will be based at Newcastle University and Newcastle upon Tyne NHS Foundation Trust. Most clinical work in the first year will be undertaken in Newcastle Community Dental Service in Kenton.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Academic Clinical Fellowships (ACFs) are 3 year fixed-term national training posts. Trainees undertake 75% clinical and 25% academic training over the term of the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ACF trainees undertake a Research Training Programme provided by the University for which funding is provided by NIHR. They also are eligible for a £1,000 bursary per year to support research training activity (eg. to attend academic conferences).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ACF trainees would also normally complete and submit an external funding application for a research fellowship to enable them to complete a higher degree (PhD or research MD) following the completion of their ACF fixed-term post,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All Academic Clinical Fellowships are run-through posts. A trainee entering ACF at DCT1 would therefore be guaranteed continued training in DCT2 and DCT3, as long as they progress satisfactorily through their training via RCP.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All applicants will be required to undertake the national clinical recruitment process and attend an assessment/interview for Dental Core Training 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In addition to a local academic interview, clinical benchmarking is required. You must complete a separate standard clinical application form during the appropriate DCT National Round. This post requires application for DCT1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications will be restricted to those candidates who meet the eligibility and entry criteria as outlined in the person specification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Health Education England working across the North East and North Cumbria operates a ‘lead employer’ arrangement and all of our Dental Core Trainees are employed by the ‘Lead Employer Trust’ hosted by Northumbria Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust for the duration of their training.&lt;/p&gt;
